HB Draft 2026 Regular Session
Abstract: Requires equal sharing of physical custody unless certain circumstances apply.
Present law (R.S. 9:335(A)(2)(b)) provides that to the extent it is feasible and in the best
interest of the child, physical custody of the child should be shared equally.
